 intend to build additional validation helpers based on the user's input, like the \"Blueprint scoring\".\n\n\n**Implementing Validation Helpers**\n\nI'm now implementing the `validateRequiredText` and `validateEmail` functions in the validation module. These helpers will ensure data integrity by enforcing required fields and correct email formats. I've designed these to work seamlessly with the existing framework. I'm taking care to ensure these are deterministic.\n\n\n**Validating the Priorities**\n\nI'm now creating validation logic for priority selection, ensuring the prioritized list is within the specified limit and not empty. I've built `validateMaxPriorities` which will be deterministic, improving the data integrity by enforcing a maximum of three priorities. It will also ensure the user selects at least one priority.\n\n\n**Validating Currency and Volume**\n\nI'm now implementing validation for non-negative currency or volume inputs with `validateNonNegativeInput`, including a safe empty state with `getSafeEmptyState`, and testing edge cases. I'm ensuring these utilities work correctly in the Phase 3 tools.\n\n\n**Calculating Shared Scores**\n\nI'm now creating pure, deterministic functions for `lib/shared-validation.ts`. I'm working on calculating Blueprint and ROI scores, ensuring standard scoring rules. I am implementing `calculateSharedBlueprintScore` and `calculateSharedROI` functions, and testing the edge cases.\n\n\n**Calculating Savings Data**\n\nI'm now integrating savings calculation functions into `lib/shared-validation.ts`, aiming for clear and deterministic helpers. I'm focusing on calculating annual hours saved, gross savings, net savings, ROI percentage, and payback months from inputs like team size, hourly rates, and investment. These are pure functions, designed for reuse and consistency across the Phase 3 tools.\n\n\n**Aligning Score Calculations**\n\nI'm now carefully aligning `calculateSharedBlueprintScore` with the existing `calculateBlueprintScore` in `lib/blueprint-data.ts`. I'm double-checking the scoring weights, including `aiMaturity`, `businessNeed`, `dataReadiness`, `processComplexity`, and `transformationReadiness`, to guarantee compatibility and accurate score generation.\n\n\n"}}
